    "narrative": "For LawDog today, our strongest plays anchor around **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (70.52) and **Tyler Freeman** (70.36), both of whom benefit from favorable park environments and manageable matchups. **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** draws J.T. Ginn in a hitter-friendly venue, and his propensity for stolen bases against a pitcher with a slow delivery provides an elite floor for our 5x5 structure. Similarly, **Tyler Freeman** is primed for production against Grant Holmes; his high park-factor adjustment and mid-order slotting make him a core offensive driver. **Daulton Varsho** (69.94) rounds out our top-tier tier, as he holds the most significant SP-advantage of the day, facing a weak opponent in Simeon Woods Richardson, which mitigates the risk typically associated with his profile.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision involved the catcher and utility spots, specifically leaving **Cal Raleigh** (50.44) on the bench. While **Cal Raleigh** projects as a serviceable bat, he draws a tough assignment against Cole Ragans; the optimizer ultimately favored the higher-upside, platoon-advantaged profiles of **Will Smith** and **Yainer Diaz**. In the middle infield, **Bryson Stott** (61.37) maintains his start primarily due to the \"SB premium\"\u2014his ability to capitalize on Eury P\u00e9rez\u2019s generous delivery gives him the edge over the slightly lower-projected **Jonathan Aranda** and **Lawrence Butler**, who were hindered by unfavorable platoon splits against left-handed starters.\n\nRisks today are dominated by the sheer volume of \"Lineup Pending\" designations, which forced our projections to rely on historical batting order assumptions. **Wenceel Perez** (48.44) and **Jeremiah Jackson** (46.18) are currently at the bottom of our efficiency threshold. **Wenceel Perez** faces the risk of a high-hold pitcher in MacKenzie Gore, and **Jeremiah Jackson** is buried at the bottom of the order, which suppresses his run-scoring probability. We will monitor official lineups closely; should **Jung Hoo Lee** or **Lawrence Butler** shift into higher-leverage spots, we may reconsider our current utility configuration to chase maximum daily efficiency.",
